    "causal_summary": "This sub-phase makes the code-graph impact/dependency/neighborhood walk reproducible across scan rebuilds at the `rankContextEdges` / `finalize()` seam in `code-graph-context.ts`, with no schema migration. Q4-C1 rank-time trust already shipped as an RRF-additive term in Wave-0. This pass implements `det-context-order-global`: baseline rank and equal-score ties now use content-derived keys (related content hash coalescing to related symbol id and stable endpoint fields), so equal-trust walks no longer inherit SQLite row order. Remaining gates: Q4-C1 boost-magnitude tuning still needs a retrieval benchmark, and the Q8 / `fuseResultsMulti` dual-channel adapter still needs an isolation-compatible shared-fuser consume path rather than a code-graph-specific fuser fork.",
